===============================================================================
| GematriaFBC 0.6; A simple gematria calculator - console ver.                |
|      readme file                                                            |
===============================================================================
This package contains 1 FreeBASIC file:

1 Main Program (./):
GematriaFBC.bas

===============================================================================
| User guide                                                                  |
===============================================================================
#####################
#   Installation    #
#####################
Linux 32- and 64-bit and Windows (32-bit) binaries are included in the Git
repository (/bin/ folder).  Each have -x86,-amd64, or .exe respectively.   If
you are unsure which Linux binary you need, download the -x86 version.

To compile on Linux:
fbc ./GematriaFBC.bas

To compile on Windows:
fbc GematriaFBC.bas

(Binaries compiled with FB version 1.02.1)

#########################
#  Running the Program  #
#########################
Linux:
It is suggested to make a symbolic link to the binary in /home/foo/bin/, that
way the program can be run from anywhere.
Windows:
Double click the .exe or call the program from the command prompt.

There are three possible option parameters
     -h, --help              Show options
     -v, --version           Show version
     -l, --log               Log session (as GematriaFBC.log)

#########################
#  General Information  #
#########################
Enter a phrase to find the gematria.  Enter !q to quit.
Gives Simple English, Regular English, Jewish, Septenary, Chaldean, Pythagorian
and Reduced.

Example:
:> GematriaFBC
Simple:      85
Regular:     510
Jewish:      244
Septenary:   43
Chaldean:    34
Pythagorian: 49
Reduced:     4
